# Pantheon — Environment Variables (optional)
#
# Pantheon uses NO hosted-LLM APIs and NO API keys. All reasoning runs through
# the local `claude` CLI (Claude Code), which you authenticate once with
# `claude` itself (e.g. `claude login`). Copy this file to .env only if you want
# to override one of the optional settings below.

# --- Claude Code backend (all optional) ---
# Override the claude binary (path or name on PATH). Defaults to `claude`.
# PANTHEON_CLAUDE_BIN=claude
# Force a specific model for headless generation. Empty => claude's own default.
# PANTHEON_DEFAULT_MODEL=
# Per-call timeout (seconds) for headless `claude -p` generation.
# PANTHEON_CLAUDE_TIMEOUT=180
# Set to 1 to disable the claude CLI entirely (used by the test suite).
# PANTHEON_NO_CLAUDE=

# --- Terminal multiplexer (optional) ---
# Force a multiplexer driver: wmux | cmux | headless. Default: auto-detect by OS.
# PANTHEON_MULTIPLEXER=

# --- GitHub integration (optional; only for real repo PRs) ---
# GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_...

# --- Platform ---
# PANTHEON_HOME=
# PANTHEON_LOG_LEVEL=INFO
# PANTHEON_MAX_ORGS=10
